    <div id="body">
    
    <div id="tribute-info">
    
    <article>
    
        <h2> The life of the ascetic artist Juan Félix Sánchez.</h2>
        
    <p> Juan Félix was a judge without studying Law, an architect without going through university classrooms, a farmer like a good Mérida man and even a politician, a matter that he soon left to deal with his passion: art. Self-taught and empirical, he was inspired by his faith, as solid as the mountains. He was born with the century, in 1900 and would die with him, in 1997.</p>

    <p>He left his studies very early and worked with his father learning the secrets of cultivating the fertile Andean lands. He also learned the art of weaving in raw wool, very typical of this cold region. His teacher would be the mother of whom he would choose as his life partner, Epifania, a silent and laborious woman who would support him to the end.</p>
        
    <p>Family with no sons, but with deep faith, as is common among the Andeans, made his first sculptural work in 1935, carvings made of marble, a Christ, the Virgin and Mary Magdalene. His best-known architectural works are, La Capilla del Filo del Tisure, dedicated to saint Dr. José Gregorio Hernández -andean like him, and La Capilla de piedra, located in San Rafael de Mucuchíes. He used the materials that the mountain offered, without altering them, just as he found them in nature. With stone, wood, and branches, without using any cement or glue, he made walls, supports, furniture, and carvings.</p>
        
    <p>He died on April 18, 1997 at the age of 96 and was buried in the Chapel of San Rafael de Mucuchíes, along with his wife Epifania. Two years after his death, the public library "Juan Félix Sánchez and Epifania Gil" was created in San Rafael de Muchuchíes. He received the National Plastic Arts Prize awarded by the National Council of Culture (CONAC) in 1988. The President of Venezuela Luis Herrera Campins (1978-83) declared the work of Juan Félix Sánchez, National Heritage.</p>

    <p>One of his most famous quote was:</p>
       
        
        
       <blockquote>"I did not do this for money and fame, at all, my ideas were always to have a work here, because one where it passes must, more than anything, leave a mark, a impression ... And when i die i will go to the site of the dreams, where i will know if my dreams were true".</blockquote>
        
        
        
    <p> To know more about this amazing artist <a id="tribute-link" href="https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Juan_F%C3%A9lix_S%C3%A1nchez" target="_blank"> follow this link. </a></p>
        
        </article>  
